Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high or the oven to 500 degrees. Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in water. Core, seed, and finely dice the @Roma tomato{1}. Cut the kernels off the @corn on the cob{1}. Core, seed, cut the @red bell pepper{1} into 1-inch cubes. Cut the @zucchini{1} into ¼-inch rounds. If the zucchini is large, cut each round into half moons. Halve the @button mushrooms{4%oz}, quartering any larger ones. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop the @parsley{1/4%oz}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the garlic, @white wine vinegar{1/2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{1%tsp}, and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thread the mushrooms, zucchini, and bell pepper onto skewers and place on a #baking sheet{}. Brush or drizzle with the marinade. Season with salt and pepper. Broil for ~{12-15%minutes}, until slightly caramelized.

> TIP: If you like your veggies extra caramelized, leave them under the broiler longer.

== Couscous ==

Make the couscous: In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} and a @salt{pinch} to a boil. Once boiling, add the @couscous{1/2%cup}, cover, and remove from heat until the rest of the meal is ready.

== Summer Corn Relish ==

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the tomato and corn to the pan and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, until the tomato breaks down. Stir in @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} and @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} and remove the pan from the heat. Once slightly cooled, stir in the @feta cheese{1/4%cup}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Finish ==

Fluff the couscous with a #fork{} and stir in the parsley, @butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Season with salt and pepper. Plate the couscous, then top with the summer corn relish and veggie skewers. Enjoy!